                                              Berlin, 13 February 1996

Dear AHG for video conformance testing,

The bitstream package hhi_burst422 contains a version of 
4:2:2-profile conformance bitstream #12.  It contains the 
following files :


  Size               path/name

11492597 hhi_burst422/hhi_burst_422_long.bits
40273920 hhi_burst422/hhi_burst_422_long.decoded
  930186 hhi_burst422/hhi_burst_422_short.bits
 3502080 hhi_burst422/hhi_burst_422_short.decoded


The bitstreams are the result of coding 4 (short) or
46 (long) frames of an 720 x 608 - window of ``Kiel Harbour''.

The most important video parameters are :

	Picture Size:	720x608
	Frame rate:	25Hz
	Bit Rate:	50 Mbps
	VBV size:	9437184 bits
	Aspect Ratio:	16x9

The picture structure is as follows :

   I-frame
   P-frame
   B-frame (burst)
   B-top-field
   B-bottom-field (burst)
   P-frame
   B-frame (burst)
   B-top-field
   B-bottom-field (burst)
   ......
	
All vectors in the bursts in B-pictures are half-pel vectors (they 
require a bilinear interpolation). The motion compensation in the 
B-frame is always field motion compensation.  In the B-fields, 
it is always 16x8 MC.

Please let us know if you have any problems decoding & matching the 
results included here.  Let us also know Your opinion, whether this 
bitstreams sufficiently tests what it intends to test.


Best regards,

M. Zhou, J. De Lameillieure

